Hard link:
1.These links point to the same file.
2.It have the same inode number.
3.They can not span over multiple filesystems.
4.It cannot be used on directories.

* Command to create a hard link is: 
 ln  [original filename] [link name] 

Soft link:
1.It is also called as a symbolic link.
2.It can link files on different filesystems.
3.It can be used on directories.

*Command to create a Soft link is: 
 ln  -s [original filename] [link name] 


